  <static seed="71" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring95.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{9x^{11}y^{9}-45y^{9}}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>9y^{9}\mathopen{}\left(x^{11}-5\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The greatest common factor is <m>9y^{9}</m>, so we can factor the polynomial as follows:</p>
<p><m>{9x^{11}y^{9}-45y^{9}}={9y^{9}\mathopen{}\left(x^{11}-5\right)}</m></p>
</solution>
